\begin_layout Chapter
The Field & Where to Be
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One of the most—if not the most—important aspects of marching is knowing
 where to march.
 Marching bands make great use of strategically placing performers to convey
 a visual style, compose shapes, and maintain uniformity.
 If the position of each performer is not explicitly defined, the band would
 not have a defined layout.
 Hence, it is important that each band member knows exactly where and when
 to be to maximize visual effect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Most marching that happens while being a member of the band will occur on
 a football field.
 While the football field is marked and designed for playing football, marching
 bands have found ways to interpret the layout and use it to their advantage
 to design a special coordinate system.
 Through this, each performer can exactly navigate to any defined position
 on the field.
 This chapter will demonstrate how to understand the field to be most familiar
 with it—marching in other places, such as in a parade, is covered in Chapter
