\begin_layout Standard
Important aspects of Attention:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This position should not cause you extreme discomfort.
 If you are experiencing exhaustion, relax your shoulders, unlock your knees,
 and keep your weight distribution even between both legs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When holding the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

imaginary trumpet
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 or other instrument that requires you to hold your instrument out in front
 of you (all except saxophones, baritones, sousaphones, drum line, and color
 guard), do not tuck your elbows.
 If you were to draw a line from your wrists down to your elbows and extend
 that line outwards, it should hit the ground away from you, on either side.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Absolutely NO TALKING.
 How can you pay attention to your leader if you are talking to the people
 around you? The main point of not talking is to maintain a mental attention
 to the leader.
\end_layout

