Receiving Feedback
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Feedback ! Receiving sandwich
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Chances are you may have never taught a large group before.
 Or, maybe you have for a really long time and feel comfortable doing it.
 Either way, you must be accepting of feedback as well.
 The band will tell you if they don't understand.
 It's up to you to interpret and parse that feedback and translate it into
 action you will do to help the band learn better.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you are looking for feedback, just ask a member of the band.
 You can ask for general feedback, or a specific question such as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is one thing that I do that you would like me to continue doing?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What is one thing that you wish I would do more of?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
