\begin_layout Standard
Start the session by warming up the band with a few simple drills.
 Either come up with some on your own or generate 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

beginner
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 or 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

easy
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 drills in the app.
 Ensure that the band has their attention on you and is ready to continue
 the rehearsal focused.
 Then begin to increase the difficulty.
 It is best to give the band drills that challenge them, but aren't impossible
 to complete.
 Practicing on that fine line between too easy and too hard yields most
 effective results and will allow the band to improve their skill most efficient
ly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I would generate the day's drills with the app before the rehearsal.
 While the app is responsive and can generate drills with any set of parameters
 and customization options, generating them on the fly may not be ideal.
 By generating before rehearsal, this allows you to review the to-be-presented
 drills and become familiar with them yourself first.
 You may find that once you get on the field and start presenting the drills,
 the band finds it too easy or too hard—that's okay.
 The app generates a set of drills, so try and pick a different drill in
 the list that seems easier or harder.
\end_layout

